data.title: Good burgers!
data.text:
Nice selection of burgers, a little pricey.
Pass on the Mac Daddy Mac and cheese.
Good, casual atmosphere for preshow eatery. Guess the BBQ is their specialty but can't comment on that. Short wait time is helpful.

data.title: I can say I've been there.
data.text: I was excited to try dinner at this place.  I had to wait, although there were empty tables.  Drinks were ok.  The menu was simple, and I didn't want to go too crazy, so I tried their burger stacked with pulled pork and brisket. Crispy onions, "donkey sauce" and bbq sauce.  Sounded good.  It was ok,  The brussel sprouts sauteed with bacon was the star of my meal.  Fresh, not overcooked and you could appreciate the vegetable.  If I get back to Louisville, I may give it another shot, because I feel I must have just caught them at an off moment.

data.title: Terribly average food and service
data.text: What a let down this place was. With a big name and being on the biggest tourist strip of Louisville I had much higher expectations. We stopped by for lunch on a Saturday, the place was fairly dead. We sat down with a group of 9 people. We all ordered cocktails, which all tasted watered down, premixed, and very average (don't get the bloody mary, there is next to nothing in it, especially alcohol). After ordering drinks (they came out in waves), we all ordered a meal. The food for 9 people took 35 minutes to come out, and the restaurant was not crowded at all. Once the food finally came out, everything was very average. The best thing was the garbage can nachos (the presentation was awesome). The burgers were slightly overcooked and most of the bbq was pretty bland. Overall, it was a huge letdown. Maybe it is because they know they have the tourists, but I definitely wouldn't waste my time here if I were in Louisville again.

data.title: A neat place on 4th St Live!
data.text:
We walked the few blocks of 4th St Live and decided on Guy's restaurant, and we were happy with our lunch!
We decided on the garbage can nachos and holy cow the portion was not a disappointment! Luckily we split the order between the two of us, we weren't able to finish them! The cheese is a homemade type of melty-cheese and is really good! The smoked pork on the nachos was awesome!! They were layered well, and had a lot of toppings.
Our server Joe was friendly and helpful with the menu, thanks Joe!
The atmosphere was great! Just from watching Guy on TV, you could see his style in the restaurant. 
Food was fair to good for portion to price. 
Great music, great server, great food: very good experience :)

data.title: Best BBQ
data.text: The atmosphere was fun and our waitress was AMAZING, she was friendly and had us laughing as we ordered.  We sat outside and loved it. I had just a regular burger. I found that for the money it wasn't anything special and was disappointing. But my husband had a burger with BBQ on it.  It was wonderful!  I tried the BBQ and found it was the best I have ever eaten.  We both loved the fry trio they were perfectly spiced and really didn't need anything added.

data.title: AWESOME PLACE TO EAT.
data.text: It was a completely awesome experience. I thought the food was good and the Nacho's are to die for. I think the drink prices are a little high but we had the specialty drinks. It gets really busy so go early or plan on waiting.

data.title: Loved it!
data.text: We had part of the restaurant reserved for a work function.  The food, drinks and service were fabulous!  The brisket and mac and cheese were awesome!

data.title: Terrible customer care
data.text: Went on a Thursday night at 630. I was told it would be an hour or less. After waiting well over an hour - I was told they had.no estimate of.how long it would be but could be as long as another hour. They just need to be honest up front. I will avoid this restaurant at all costs as I like to deal with honest restaurants.

data.title: Late lunch with my wife
data.text: Made the trip downtown to try out Guy Fieri's smoke house ... atmosphere is good . Staff is very friendly and attentive. . We arrived a little after 2pm so no wait .. we ordered a smokehouse burger and a mac and cheese  Burger. Both are big sandwiches.  Good but expected some better flavor. .. maybe a bigger flavor profile. . Would recommend if in the area..

data.title: Interesting place
data.text: Daughter and I weren't very hungry so we went just for appetizers. The pork rinds she ordered were disappointing because there wasn't anything else with them - just pork rinds with a little seasoning o them. Not bad tasting, just very plain. The Gouda fondue and pretzel cigars were very good! Tasty! Good, quick service. The rest of the menu looked good if we had wanted a full meal. Barbeque smelled good.

data.title: Not what I expected
data.text: I went here on Business. My first problem, was the hostess sat me and no service, had to ask her again. Waiter said that someone didn't show up and they sat me at a table with no server. Once I got service it was good. I thought the food was alright but I think I expected more. The barbecue sauce on the table, to me tasted like ketchup. I would give it another try incase it was an off night.

data.title: Good Food and Happy hour
data.text: I was alone and sat at the bar, otherwise it was an hour wait.  It was a really busy night but the service was great.  This fit in perfectly with the Fourth Street Experience.

data.title: Good food
data.text: We always like to eat a different places when out of town. Outside seating was neat and fries were awesome! I would say try nachos they come out in a cool neat way.

data.title: Good, but would not be on triple D
data.text:
I was excited to try one of Guy's restaurants, but this was obviously just his name on the building. 

Great atmosphere, good food but just not the WOW factor I had hoped. 

If I had to put them in a category I would say Applebee's or Chilli's.   Food was good, service was decent, price was decent. 

The food people were getting around me looked   Good with decent portions but again now WOW. 

The Bacon Mac And cheese burger looked like it was from Red Robin. 

The bad:  1:05 minute wait for seating and 1 hour wait for food.  Ran out of rolled silverware and gave me Togo package with fork and knife, this is bad in my book, very bad. 

I'd be more likely to frequent this place for lunch.

data.title: Pretty Good
data.text: Great atmosphere. Had great service. I will say that 4th Street can get a little wild so don't take little kids too late. Food was really good with lots of choices. Will go back next time we are in town. Brick burger and Mac & Cheese Burger

data.title: Family dinner
data.text: Love the atmosphere and energy of this place.   Menu has many offerings for different tastes but the only down fall - No kids menu.  And during our visit there were several families with kids.   I also wish they offered small house salads or something to go with my meal in place of a large dinner salad.   The sandwich my husband ordered wasn't available as they were out of it so he had to order something different.    Overall the food was great.   Still a few kinks to work but we will return and hopefully they won't be out of what we want. 👍

data.title: So so
data.text:
We love Guy and Food Network and we're thrilled to see he had a restaurant here in Louisville.  We travel here a few times a year.  

Guy would have had a heart attack if her dined with us.  It was loud (ok understandable) but we waited forever to order a drink.  We ordered the jalapeño enfused tequila and the first round was amazing.  After we ordered our food the second round is drinks came and they were 90 percent mix.  Totally different color and taste.  We sent them back and they they brought the same garbage back.  

The salmon was ok and the turkey burger was really good, juicy and tender.  This place has a lot of promise but as delivered was a loser.  Guy needs to spend some time here and see what is really going on.  We will come back and try again in the future but we're dissatisfied with this experience.

data.title: Name only
data.text: It's to be expected, you're paying for the name. I was there for a show, and I did like the patio had great view of the stage. I did think the pricing was high, but that was to be expected. I ordered the turkey burger, and it was good. Did I think it was worth the price no. I thought the turkey burger was good, but thought the cranberry sauce on it was overpowering. It would have been great without it. The service was good. I'm glad I tried it but it wouldn't be a go to spot.

data.title: Nothing special
data.text: The wife and I decided to give this place a try since we've been seeing a lot about it on the local news. We went a little after 3 to beat the dinner crowd and was seated immediately. The place is decorated nicely in the server and I think's name was Scott was extremely nice. The wife ordered the smokehouse burger which came with fries and I had something like a sampler platter of barbecue pulled pork, beef brisket,   sausage, and coleslaw. I also got a side of macaroni and cheese and brussels sprouts with bacon. My wife said her burger was very good, my dinner was OK nothing special. The beef brisket was really good, the pulled pork was a little too dry, and the ribs I didn't care for because I really don't like barbecue rubbing on him I would prefer them wet. On the other hand the two sides I ordered was very good. The macaroni and cheese was almost as good as my mothers and I really like the brussels sprouts with bacon. I probably wouldn't go back but it was nice to say I've been there.

data.title: It's just ok
data.text: I was extremely disappointed in the amount of time it took to get my food. The food was just average. I had the triple crown.  Also the channel was changed in the bar without asking if we were watching. Extremely disappointed in the service!
